Police consider roadside bathroom break a no no
Comment
By Diane Turbyfill dturbyfill@gastongazette.com
Gaston Gazette
By Diane Turbyfill dturbyfill@gastongazette.com
Posted May. 3, 2016 at 7:56 AM
Updated at 7:56 AM
By Diane Turbyfill dturbyfill@gastongazette.com
Posted May. 3, 2016 at 7:56 AM
A Gastonia man was arrested after police say he parked in the middle of the street for a bathroom break.The incident happened just before 1 a.m. Tuesday.A Gastonia police officer reported seeing a car stopped on Radio Street near North Morris Street. The driver was outside urinating, the officer wrote on the police report.Eleazar Panfillo Hernandez, 43, of North Ransom Street, was taken to Gaston County Jail where officers say he refused to take a breath test.The officer said Hernandez smelled of alcohol and was unsteady on his feet.Hernandez's blood was taken to determine if he was impaired.He was charged with DWI, possession of an open container and driving with a revoked license, not related to impaired driving.He was jailed on a $3,000 bond.
By Diane Turbyfill dturbyfill@gastongazette.com
